http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 27 Aug 2015
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2015; 28(35) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=18422


Anthrax, Kenya
--------------
Information received on [and dated] 27 Aug 2015 from Dr Kisa J Z Juma Ngeiywa, CVO Director of Veterinary Services, State Department of Livestock; Directorate of Veterinary Services, Ministry of Agriculture, Livestock and Fisheries, Nairobi, Kenya

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 10 Jul 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 13 Jul 2015
Report date: 27 Aug 2015
Date submitted to OIE: 27 Aug 2015
Reason for notification: unexpected change in the distribution or increase in morbidity or mortality of a listed disease
Summary description: the disease occurred in Lake Nakuru National Park with a population of about 4500 buffaloes resulting in the death of 300.
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: _Bacillus anthracis_
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: contact with infected animal(s) at grazing/watering
Epidemiological comments: unusual mortalities were reported in Lake Nakuru National Park in buffaloes, occurring near the lake shore, watering holes and the fence line on 10 Jul 2015. Also affected were rhinos, Rothschild giraffes, elands, impalas, warthogs, and Thomson gazelles with low mortalities.

Increased distribution
Disease impact
Increased / Province [County] / Species / Change
Incidence / Rift Valley [Nakuru] / African buffalo (Cape buffalo): Bovidae (_Syncerus caffer_) / 1 to 4
Morbidity / Rift Valley [Nakuru]/ African buffalo (Cape buffalo): Bovidae (_Syncerus caffer_) / 1 to 4
Mortality / Rift Valley [Nakuru] / African buffalo (Cape buffalo): Bovidae(Syncerus caffer) / 1 to 4

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; disinfection/disinfestation; quarantine; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; official disposal of carcasses, by-products and waste; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Nakuru Regional Veterinary Investigation Laboratory (local laboratory) / African buffalo (Cape buffalo) / optical microscopy / 13 Jul 2015 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

